  "reasoning": "The bug report (bugzilla #207835) describes that backlight control doesn't work on the Acer TravelMate 5735Z by default, but works with 'acpi_backlight=native'. The issue is that the video_detect_dmi_table array in drivers/acpi/video_detect.c is missing a DMI quirk entry to force native backlight for this specific laptop model. The default autodetection selects ACPI video backlight (because ACPI_VIDEO_BACKLIGHT is available), but the ACPI video interface is broken on this hardware - it shows the OSD but doesn't change actual brightness. The fix requires adding a DMI quirk entry with callback=video_detect_force_native matching DMI_SYS_VENDOR='Acer', DMI_PRODUCT_NAME='TravelMate 5735Z', and DMI_BOARD_NAME='BA51_MV'. This exact fix was later added to the Linux kernel (visible in newer versions at lines 703-711 with explicit reference to bugzilla 207835)."
}

